WHO   — The Nuclear Shell Model — The NUCLEUS has its OWN shells: protons and neutrons each fill quantized levels inside the core, with 'magic numbers' (2, 8, 20, 28, 50, 82, 126) marking filled shells and extra-stable nuclei. Held by the STRONG force (Goeppert-Mayer & Jensen, Nobel 1963).
WHAT  — The NUCLEUS has its OWN shells: protons and neutrons each fill quantized levels inside the core, with 'magic numbers' (2, 8, 20, 28, 50, 82, 126) marking filled shells and extra-stable nuclei. Held by the STRONG force (Goeppert-Mayer & Jensen, Nobel 1963).
WHERE — ATM · The Atom  Framework inputs: the Standard Model & atomic/nuclear physics  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — IS NUCLEAR STABILITY. Magic-number nuclei (helium-4, oxygen-16, calcium-40, lead-208) are unusually stable; the model predicts decay, abundance, and the 'island of stability.' Transitions cost ~MeV → gamma rays. This is the NUCLEAR shell system — a MILLION times more energetic than the electronic one.
